295
00:14:27,349 --> 00:14:28,902
- What are you a doctor now?

296
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:31,974
- It doesn't take a doctor
to see what a mess you're in.

297
00:14:32,112 --> 00:14:33,596
- I did see a white light.

298
00:14:33,734 --> 00:14:36,530
No, no, that was Sinatra
singing at the Sands.

299
00:14:36,668 --> 00:14:39,085
No, no, maybe that
was just a paramedic

300
00:14:39,223 --> 00:14:42,467
shocking me back to
life, huh? [laughs]

301
00:14:42,605 --> 00:14:44,607
- You know the lack of
oxygen to your brain

302
00:14:44,745 --> 00:14:46,471
has not affected your sarcasm.

303
00:14:48,094 --> 00:14:49,129
What it is with you Briefcase,

304
00:14:49,267 --> 00:14:50,682
how can you be so smart

305
00:14:50,820 --> 00:14:53,720
and not see how bad
your situation is?

306
00:14:53,858 --> 00:14:57,517
- I guess it's the same way
you call shrimp jumbo. [laughs]

307
00:14:57,655 --> 00:14:59,760
- I don't know how
to tell you this.

308
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:02,729
But in Dr. Thompson's opinion,

309
00:15:02,867 --> 00:15:04,213
you only have a year to live,

310
00:15:04,351 --> 00:15:06,008
